.  It is where I saw my friends die at the hand of Drelzna!<br>
<br>
We entered that place of the damned, seeking adventure and the riches Drelzna possessed.  It was just us three.  Glenwise, a seasoned Scout who had much knowledge; Selah, a Ranger with great bravery and speed, wife of Glenwise; and myself, Qenanya, a charming Keeper of the Craft.  We had shared many battles and adventures together and our confidence was high.  Maybe too high.<br>
<br>
Glenwise lead us to the lair of Rathyl as if the path was an old memory.  I never questioned where he gets his knowledge of these places or the creatures within.  Some things are better left unquestioned.  &quot;What is our purpose for visiting Rathyl?&quot; I asked.  &quot;We need the keys the she carries, one for each of us.&quot; was Glenwise's reply.  I laughed.  Why would we each need a key, one should be enough?  My laughter later turned to tears.<br>
<br>
Having mysterious knowledge of Rathyl's abode, Glenwise layed out our battle plans, and we soon aquired the needed keys along with a few other treasures.  We moved out to a relatively safe spot and rested.  There we made plans for Drelzna.<br>
<br>
It was a simple plan, not unlike many other battles we have fought before.  A simple plan, but even simple plans can go wrong.<br>
<br>
We attacked and things seemed to be going well.  The necromancer flunkies where mesmerized by my beauty, Drelzna was nervous from hearing the barking of Tashan, and her limbs were like molasses from the dweomers I cast.  She was loosing health fast from Glenwise and Selah's fury.  It came time to work my spells again, but something went wrong, and I found myself faced with two very angry necromancers!  During my struggle, Drelzna took a personal dislike with Glenwise, and he went down fast under her assault.  I was stunned from his death!  After what seemed an eternity, I finally got the flunkies back under control only to see Selah fall!<br>
<br>
NO!!!  This cannot be!!  I quickly cast my dweomer and had Drelzna staring at my beauty.  I knew I was next to fall.  This cannot happen!  Quickly I searched my spell book, finding the spell I needed.  Curse my memory!  I never seem to be able to remember all the spells I need.  I stood up, and spoke the words of friendship and love, and soon one of the flunkies was mine to control.  I immediately sent her to attack Drelzna while I dealt with the other flunky.  Soon Drelzna fell, already being near death from Glenwise's and Selah's bravery.  As I quickly searched my book for the needed Gate spell to get me out of there, the other flunkie came to her senses, and cast horrible magics on me.  I was tired, exausted, and knew my time was running out.  I barely had the energy for one more casting.  Thankfully, my newly charmed friend immediately came to my aid, giving me the necessary time to cast and escape with only a sliver of my health.<br>
<br>
I mourned the loss of my friends.  Never will I view that place of evil the same.  One day Drelzna will die many deaths at my hand for her treachery!<br>
<br>
----------------------------<br>
<br>
I often get asked why I never have gate memmed.  As an enchanter, it is a rare moment for me to need it, and never during battle.  I need all the spell slots for the needs and survivability of the group.<br>
